    {
      "title": "1. Introduction & Definitions",
      "blocks": [],
      "subsections": [
        {
          "title": "1.1 Multimodal Model Evolution Stages",
          "blocks": [
            {
              "type": "markdown",
              "text": "We use the following **precise, architecture-first definitions** throughout this list. Understanding these distinctions is critical for correctly classifying modern models."
            }
          ],
          "subsections": [
            {
              "title": "Traditional Multimodal Models",
              "blocks": [
                {
                  "type": "markdown",
                  "text": "<img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Category-Traditional-1d4ed8?style=flat-square\" alt=\"Traditional category\"> <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Focus-Alignment%20%26%20Fusion-2563eb?style=flat-square\" alt=\"Alignment and Fusion\">\n> *Pre-2023 mainstream era*\n\nIndependent per-modality processing followed by simple fusion (early, late, or hybrid). No large-scale language model backbone. Focuses on representation alignment, cross-modal retrieval, and captioning. Examples: CLIP, ALIGN, ViLBERT, BLIP."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "title": "Multimodal Large Language Models (MLLMs)",
              "blocks": [
                {
                  "type": "markdown",
                  "text": "<img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Category-MLLM-2563eb?style=flat-square\" alt=\"MLLM category\"> <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Pattern-Modular%20Late%20Fusion-1e40af?style=flat-square\" alt=\"Modular late fusion\">\n> *Modular Late-Fusion paradigm*\n\nCombine a **frozen or fine-tuned pretrained vision encoder** (e.g., ViT/CLIP) with a **pretrained LLM** (e.g., LLaMA, Vicuna) via a lightweight **projector/adapter** (e.g., MLP, Q-Former). The vision encoder and LLM are **not jointly trained from scratch**. Understanding-only (no native image generation).\n\nKey characteristics:\n- ✅ Pretrained vision encoder (frozen or fine-tuned)\n- ✅ Pretrained LLM backbone\n- ✅ Projector layer (MLP / Q-Former / cross-attention)\n- ❌ No joint pretraining from scratch\n- ❌ No native image generation\n\nExamples: **LLaVA**, **Qwen-VL**, **InternVL**, **MiniCPM-V**, **mPLUG-Owl**"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "title": "Unified Multimodal Models (UMMs)",
              "blocks": [
                {
                  "type": "markdown",
                  "text": "<img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Category-UMM-7c3aed?style=flat-square\" alt=\"UMM category\"> <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Focus-Understanding%20%2B%20Generation-6d28d9?style=flat-square\" alt=\"Understanding and generation\">\n> *Single framework for Understanding + Generation (U+G)*\n\nA **single model** that handles both image understanding and image generation within one framework. May still rely on pretrained components (vision encoder, LLM, modular tokenizers), but unifies the U+G pipeline. The defining feature is **U+G unification**, not necessarily training from scratch.\n\nKey characteristics:\n- ✅ Unified understanding + generation\n- ✅ Single model / shared weights\n- ⚠️ May use pretrained vision/language components\n- ⚠️ May use modular / decoupled tokenizers\n\nExamples: **Show-o**, **Emu3**, **Janus**, **BAGEL**, **BLIP3-o**"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "title": "Native Multimodal Models (NMMs)",
              "blocks": [
                {
                  "type": "markdown",
                  "text": "<img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Category-NMM-b91c1c?style=flat-square\" alt=\"NMM category\"> <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Constraint-Trained%20from%20Scratch-991b1b?style=flat-square\" alt=\"Trained from scratch\">\n> *Jointly trained from scratch — no pretrained backbone*\n\n**The strictest category.** NMMs are trained **jointly from scratch on all modalities** — they do **not** rely on any pretrained LLM or pretrained vision encoder as initialization. All parameters are learned end-to-end from raw multimodal data.\n\nKey characteristics:\n- ✅ No pretrained LLM backbone\n- ✅ No pretrained vision encoder\n- ✅ All components jointly trained from scratch\n- ✅ Input: text tokens + image patches/tokens\n- ✅ Output: text (understanding focus; generation optional)\n\nNMMs are further divided by **fusion architecture**:\n\n##### NMM — Early Fusion\nMultimodal interaction begins **from the first layer**. A **single Transformer decoder** processes tokenized text and continuous/discrete image patches together, with **minimal modality-specific parameters** (only a linear patchify layer for images). No separate image encoder is maintained.\n\n- Single unified Transformer (decoder-only)\n- Continuous image patches or minimal discrete tokenization\n- Modality interaction from layer 1\n- Near-zero modality-specific parameters (excluding linear patch embed)\n- Examples: **Chameleon**, **Emu3** (if trained from scratch), **Transfusion**\n\n##### NMM — Late Fusion\nEach modality is first processed by a **dedicated unimodal component** (e.g., a vision tower or image encoder), but these components are **jointly trained from scratch** (not pretrained). Cross-modal interaction occurs at **deeper layers**.\n\n- Separate unimodal processing stages (trained from scratch)\n- Cross-modal interaction at deeper layers\n- More modality-specific parameters\n- Examples: Models with jointly-trained vision encoders → decoder interaction"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "title": "MoE Routing in NMMs",
              "blocks": [
                {
                  "type": "markdown",
                  "text": "<img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Routing-MoE-6b21a8?style=flat-square\" alt=\"MoE routing\"> <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Variants-Modality--Agnostic%20%7C%20Modality--Aware-7e22ce?style=flat-square\" alt=\"MoE variants\">"
                },
                {
                  "type": "table",
                  "ref": "1-introduction-definitions.11-multimodal-model-evolution-stages.moe-routing-in-nmms.table3"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "title": "1.2 Scope & Taxonomy",
          "blocks": [
            {
              "type": "markdown",
              "text": "```\nMultimodal Models\n├── Traditional Multimodal Models                    [§2]\n│   ├── Contrastive (CLIP, SigLIP, ALIGN)\n│   ├── Generative Pretraining (BLIP series)\n│   └── Fusion: Early / Late / Hybrid\n│\n├── Multimodal LLMs (MLLMs) — Modular Late Fusion    [§3]\n│   ├── Pretrained Vision Encoder + Projector + LLM\n│   └── Understanding Only\n│\n├── Unified Multimodal Models (UMMs) — U+G           [§4]\n│   ├── Diffusion-Based\n│   ├── Autoregressive (AR)\n│   │   ├── Pixel-Encoding\n│   │   └── Semantic-Encoding\n│   ├── Hybrid AR + Diffusion\n│   └── Any-to-Any / Omni <kbd>Omni</kbd>\n│\n└── Native Multimodal Models (NMMs) — Scratch        [§5]\n    ├── Early Fusion (single Transformer, minimal modality params)\n    ├── Late Fusion (separate components, all from scratch)\n    ├── MoE-Based\n    │   ├── Modality-Agnostic Routing\n    │   └── Modality-Aware Routing\n    └── Advanced: Omni <kbd>Omni</kbd> / Any-to-Any / Hybrid AR+Diffusion\n```"
            }
          ],
          "subsections": []
        },
        {
          "title": "Tag Legend",
          "blocks": [
