    {
      "title": "How to Contribute",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "markdown",
          "text": "We welcome contributions! Please follow these guidelines:"
        }
      ],
      "subsections": [
        {
          "title": "Validation Rules",
          "blocks": [
            {
              "type": "markdown",
              "text": "**For NMM submissions (strict):**\n- [ ] Confirm the model does **NOT** use any pretrained LLM backbone\n- [ ] Confirm the model does **NOT** use any pretrained vision encoder (CLIP, ViT, etc.)\n- [ ] All weights are jointly trained from scratch on multimodal data\n- [ ] Classify as Early Fusion or Late Fusion (both must be \"from scratch\")\n\n**For UMM submissions:**\n- [ ] Confirm the model handles both image understanding AND image generation\n- [ ] Note whether pretrained components are used (annotate accordingly)\n\n**For MLLM submissions:**\n- [ ] Note which vision encoder is used (must be a pretrained encoder)\n- [ ] Note which LLM backbone is used (must be a pretrained LLM)"
            }
          ],
          "subsections": []
        },
        {
          "title": "Entry Format",
          "blocks": [
            {
              "type": "markdown",
              "text": "```markdown\n| **Model Name** | [Paper](arxiv_link) [Code](github_link) [HF](huggingface_link) BADGES | Scale | Key contribution / notes |\n```"
            },
            {
              "type": "markdown",
              "text": "**Recommended tags:** `<kbd>Open</kbd>` open weights · `<kbd>Closed</kbd>` closed/industry · `<kbd>Efficient</kbd>` lightweight or deployment-focused · `<kbd>Omni</kbd>` any-to-any or omni-modal · `<kbd>Generation</kbd>` generation-capable · `<kbd>Video</kbd>` video-centric · `<kbd>Analysis</kbd>` survey or analysis paper\n\nSubmit a PR with:\n1. The paper/model entry in the correct section\n2. A one-line justification for the chosen category\n3. Links to paper, code, and/or weights"
            }
          ],
          "subsections": []
        }
      ]
    },
